Mexico Said to Hire Three Banks for Meetings With Japan Bond Investors

-- B y   Y u s u k e   M i y a z a w a
-- 
2011-08-22T03:15:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-22/mexico-said-to-hire-three-banks-for-meetings-with-japan-bond-investors.html
Mexico  hired three banks to arrange
meetings with bond investors in Japan next week, according to a
person with direct knowledge of the matter.  Citigroup Inc., Mitsubishi UFJ Morgan Stanley Securities
Co. and Nomura Holdings Inc. are organizing the talks, said the
person, who asked not to be identified as the information is
private.  Mexico is rated Baa1 by Moody’s Investors Service, the risk
assessor’s third lowest investment grade ranking, and BBB by
Standard & Poor’s, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yusuke Miyazawa in Tokyo at 
 ymiyazawa3@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
 Shelley Smith  at 
 ssmith118@bloomberg.net . 